Loved chatting to these three amazing Sweat trainers about their new programs yesterday on @Sweat's IG live! I especially loved that I finally got to introduce you all to Sweat's newest trainer, Monica! 💛

We spoke about all things HIIT, why we love it and what each new program is about! We also chatted a little about what #SweatMade means to us, as well as launched a SWEAT COMPETITION giving you the chance to WIN one of 20 spots to a virtual training session with all four of us trainers 🔥! Take a listen to find out more and stay tuned across @Sweat's Instagram for the details on how to enter! 

More info: get.sweat.com/sweat-made

@ChontelDuncan, @BritanyWilliams, @trainwithmon - thanks for taking the time to chat with us! 🌟

If you want to try any of our new programs, download @Sweat using the 7 day free trial today!

www.kaylaitsines.com/CardioandAbs

In this episode of my 'How To' series, I show you exactly how to set up AND dismantle the squat rack! 🏋️‍♀️

Now if you think this piece of equipment is VERY intimating... you're definitely not alone! I'm sure there's a lot of women that avoid using the squat rack when they are in the gym... and that is exactly why I have started this video series. 

BUT I want you to take me with you to the gym next time, and give yourself the time to get comfortable using the Squat Rack. And if you still feel uncomfortable, bring a friend to the gym with you so you can both learn how to use this machine together.... I promise it's not as intimidating as it looks! 🙂

This machine is used in my new High Intensity Strength Program, so if you love this machine OR if you've never used it before and want to start - I recommend my new and improved gym program for you! You can try it today by downloading @Sweat via the link in my bio! 

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntesnityStrengthWithKayla

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #Workout #GymWorkout

node.text:
In episode 3 of of my 'How To' series, I'm showing you exactly how to set up and use a resistance band! 😄

There are so many types of resistance bands that can be used for many different exercises, but I want to show you how you can attach longer resistance bands to a bar to help you with things like assisted pull-ups and chin-ups!

You will usually find resistance bands hanging up around the gym, or you can bring your own to ensure you've got the right size available for you. ✔️

The key thing to remember with resistance bands is that the THICKER bands have MORE resistance than the thinner bands. In the case of a pull-up or chin up, the thicker band will assist you more (as there is more resistance) making it easier for you to pull yourself up to complete the exercise.

However, in most other cases (like resistance band tricep extensions or bicep curls) the thinner resistance bands actually make the exercise easier than the thicker ones! And if this confuses you a little bit, don't worry! You will instantly feel the difference and know which one is right to use when you try them out. 😅

I hope this video gives you the confidence to try an assisted pull-up or chin-up next time you are in the gym! I have included these in my new High Intensity Strength Program, which you can try by downloading @Sweat today! 

#SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatApp #SweatCommunity #gym #gymworkout

node.text:
Episode ✌️ of my 'How To' series is all about how to use the Cable & Pulley machine! 
This machine can look quite intimidating at first because there are so many parts to it. I've heard my clients say that they used to walk up to the machine and use whatever attachment is already there because they are too scared (or don't know how) to change them... which I totally understand.

Hopefully, this video will help you gain the confidence to firstly... use this machine, and secondly... use the machine exactly the way you want to! So next time you're in the gym, take me with you and give yourself the time to learn how these parts actually work. I promise it's easier than you have imagined! 😊

My High Intensity Strength program includes the use of this machine, and the @Sweat app will tell you exactly which attachment you need to complete the exercise which should help you build confidence, too! You can try my new gym program today via the link in my bio 😊

PS. All the videos that I will be sharing over the next week have been filmed before Adelaide's current lockdown. Stay safe ❤️

#SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #SweatApp #Workout #Gym #gymworkout 

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text:
INTRODUCING MY NEW 'HOW TO' SERIES - GYM EDITION 🌟
As gyms begin to re-open around the world, I want everyone to feel confident and comfortable getting back to their gym-based workouts.

I also know a lot of women feel intimidated about going to the gym, especially when it comes to using large equipment... so it's for these reasons I want to show you exactly HOW TO navigate a gym setting. In this series, I'll be taking you the step-by-step process as to how to set up and use different equipment around the gym.

To kick the series off, we're starting with the equipment that was requested most by YOU, #SWKCommunity...  THE LEG PRESS! 

We have a variety of gym-based programs in the @Sweat app that involves using the Leg Press, including my new and improved High-Intensity Strength program. So, next time you're in the gym... I want you to take me with you and allow yourself the time to get comfortable with using these bigger machines. Before you know it, you'll wish you stopped avoiding them sooner! 

I hope by the end of this episode you feel a lot LESS intimidated and a lot MORE empowered to use this machine in your training. 

If you're keen to start using the Leg Press in your workouts, I recommend trying my new and improved High Intensity Strength program. It uses larger machines, free weights and bodyweight exercises to help women get fitter and get stronger! You can try it today for free using @Sweat's 7-Day free trial (link in bio)!

It has been great to bring you even more new gym programs to Sweat and from now on we will be working with @iFIT to help deliver even more choice and variety to you all!

#SWK #SweatwithKayla #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #LegPress #gym #gymequipment #gymtutorial

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text: Let’s do this!! Take me anywhere with you and let’s train abs together !! (No equipment) EXPRESS WORKOUT

"But Kayla, I don't have time to workout today!!" 
... are you sure about that?! 🤣🤣

If this sounds like you, I'm here to tell you that there is almost ALWAYS time to squeeze in a workout! You just have to start telling yourself that any amount of time working out it's worth it! 
 
I've created this 5-minute "follow-along" lower body workout that should have you breaking a sweat and feeling accomplished in a short amount of time! I'm ready to work out with you right now, but it's up to YOU to set aside the time to get your body moving today! 

✅ Squat Pulse - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

✅ Curtsey Lunge - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

✅ Glute Bridge Walkout - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

 Do 3 laps

✅ Squat Pulse finisher - 30 secs

I certainly felt the burn after that!! Did you? 🔥😅

If you love the thought of an express workout - there are SO many incredible programs in the @Sweat app that are ready and waiting for you! Head to the link in my bio for a 7-Day free trial and get moving today!

Are your glute bridges actually working your glutes? Or just hurting your lower back? 🤔
Glute bridges are one of those exercises that look quite easy to do... but they can hurt the wrong muscles if done incorrectly! 

I've noticed that some people push their hips as high as they can, causing them to over-extend and put pressure on their lower back. If this sounds like you, or you haven't been feeling the burn in your glutes when doing glute bridges, I want you to watch this video and practice my number one tip! 

You should absolutely be feeling your glutes burn if you do this! 🔥
Let me know if this has helped you!

node.text:
This is an easy one to get wrong ❌ 
So if you do Ab Bikes often, I want you to take the time to learn how to get them right! ✅

In this video, I break down the exercise into smaller steps to help you perfect your form. Once you've mastered each movement, add each step in until you build up to a full Ab Bike! 

Here are some do's and don'ts to remember:
DO
✅Rest hands in front of ears
✅Rotate at the torso
✅Bring knees in close to the chest
✅Extend your legs in a push and pull motion
✅Elevate your shoulders

DON'T
❌Pull your neck up with your hands behind your head
❌Do small in and out motions with your legs
❌Curve your back away from the floor

What other exercises do you want to learn from me? Comment below!

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatwithKayla

node.text:
Right, so today I'm going to break down the burpee for you to make it easier.

It's still not going to be EASY (it's a burpee haha!!)... but these tips will make it easier to do 😅⁣ You're still going to #SweatwithKayla and you'll find burpees in my High Intensity program. There's a link in my bio for a 7 day FREE trial of the @Sweat app. 

Follow this and see how it feels:
✅Start at the top of your mat
✅Put your hands down in front of your feet as you squat down
✅Jump back into a push up position
✅Make sure your wrist and shoulder is in line
✅Back nice and straight
✅Make sure you're stable and have a strong core 
✅Jump back in with feet apart (not together!)
✅Stand up and do your jump
✅Find your rhythm

Some common mistakes:
❌Starting with your hands too far in front of you 
❌Not holding your core tight throughout each movement
❌Letting your back dip down into an unstable position
❌Jumping in too far with your feet and putting pressure on your knees
❌Arching your back too much before jumping to a standing position

Now, I've shown you the correct technique how do your burpees feel?

node.text:
For a lot of women around the world, the last 12 months have been tough. For many of you it meant an adjustment to working out at home, or perhaps, it meant losing the time, space or motivation to work out all together. I want you to know that you’re not alone in facing these challenges. We see you and and at @Sweat we want to help.

I want to introduce you to Sweat’s new MOVE AGAIN programs, designed specifically for those who have had a break in their fitness journey due to the pandemic.

These four new beginner level programs consist of two 20-minute workouts a week for four weeks and are led by four inspiring trainers that are dedicated to help you form healthy habits and get you back into fitness. 

👉 Bodyweight Strength with Anissia (@avh__fitness)
🌟 When Anissia isn’t playing basketball, she’s all about strength and bodyweight circuits. Her approach to fitness is all about getting back to basics and her Bodyweight Strength workouts require absolutely no equipment.

👉 Low Impact HIIT with Samantha (@so_manti)
🌟 With Samantha you can expect a fast-paced and upbeat style to her Low Impact HIIT workouts which are perfect for getting a quick sweat up in a short amount of time.

👉 Strength & Cardio with Marilyn (@fitwithmarilyn)
🌟 Marilyn’s approach to fitness is about maximising your time with fun and dynamic workouts to help you build form and to find your love for moving again. You’ll feel strong off the back of these workouts and the combination of rep based strength and timed based cardio.

👉 Low Impact Strength with Kelsey (@kelseywells)
🌟 Now Kelsey is one of my best friends and she has been part of the Sweat family for a while now and we so are excited to be adding a low-impact strength program. Kelsey’s new dumbbell based workouts are great to build your confidence using weights and will have you feeling strong again in no time.

We’ve designed each program to support your physical and mental health. We want you to remember how good it feels to move again!

So why not take advantage of our Sweat 7-day free trial and start moving again

www.kaylaitsines.com/moveagain

#MoveAgain #Sweat #Sweatcommunity #SWKcommunity #KaylaItsines

node.text:
ARNA BEING THE CUTEST!!! 
That's it . . . that's the post. 🤣

Just kidding! 😜 This is us going to our local coffee shop to get a babycino and marshmallow for her, and my heart can't deal with it!! I have pretty much the same routine every weekend, and it involves lots of family, friends, Arna, and a whole lot of coffee! ☕🤣

We always do our friends and family breakfast at either of our two favourite cafes in Adelaide, so we can all just sit down and catch up about our weeks over delicious food. Arna is normally running around having the best time, which means someone always has to be on the lookout for ‘Arna Patrol’ (basically just keeping her out of trouble). 🤣

I’ll normally spend the rest of the day cleaning whilst Arna sleeps, seeing my grandparents for more coffee, and then heading to dinner at my parent’s house. Then, it’s movie night and bed! Very low key weekend - it’s probably very different to other people’s weekends, but it feels wholesome and I love it 😝

#SWKcommunity, I want to hear how you spend your weekends off! Share it with the community below 👇

#SweatwithKayla #SWK #SweatCommunity #RestDays #Coffee #Weekend #Brunch #Cafe #Breakfast #Family

HIIT CARDIO & ABS - FULL BODY WORKOUT 💥 Yes, my new program is finally here!! I’m so excited to launch this program, and I just know that all you HIIT fans out there are going to love it!!

This program is designed to be quick, fast, but highly efficient! There are 3 weekly 30-minute workouts plus express options, so perfect for you ladies who want to still fit a great workout into your busy lifestyles. It's suitable for an intermediate level of fitness, and is exactly how I like to train: fast, intense, and fun! HIIT workouts are challenging, but will absolutely leave you feeling energised and strong by the end of it! And of course, you are going to feel the BURN with these core focused workouts!! 🔥

For this workout, you’ll only need dumbbells and a bench or chair. This program is designed to be completed at home with minimal equipment, or at the gym, wherever works best for YOU! 💪

CIRCUIT ONE:
✔️Dumbbell Burpee (10 reps)
✔️3-Way Mountain Climber (30 seconds)

CIRCUIT TWO:
✔️Push-Up & Side Plank (12 reps, 6 per side)
✔️X Hop (30 seconds)

CIRCUIT THREE: 
✔️​​Single-Leg Hip Thrust (60 seconds, 30 seconds per side)
✔️Decline Shoulder Tap (30 seconds)
✔️Sit-Up & Clap (30 seconds)

Complete three laps of each circuit!

Can’t wait to get started with this new HIIT program?! Head to the link in bio and download the @Sweat app today to try a 7 day free trial, and let me know how you go! 🤗

#SweatMade #fitness #SweatwithKayla #SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #Workout #HIIT #HighItensityTraining #Gym #Abs

AND I AM SO PROUD OF ALL OF YOU LADIES!! 🧡

I have absolutely LOVED seeing all of you sharing your #SweatMade stories! 😍It's not all just about the physical changes you get from fitness, it's about how you FEEL about yourself, and being proud of that! Even more than this, I love that you ladies are reflecting on yourselves, and putting a spotlight on your own #SweatMade words. I want you to be giving your self-worth a workout at the same time, and sometimes we don't take the time to take a look at how we have grown along the journey. 

I want you to feel as good on the inside as you do on the outside! And I want you to be proud of everything that you have worked towards, and celebrate that!! 

YOU ARE ALL THESE #SWEATMADE WORDS AND MORE!! I want to see YOUR #SweatMade stories, so keep it going #SWKCommunity 🙌

We are #SweatMade. Are you? 

#SWK #SweatwithKayla #Progress #Fitness #SweatCommunity 

@sweat.and.sweet @getfit.elia @s.tania.l.a @moorebalanced @arny_life

node.text:
OW! Who knew that your abs could burn this much?! 🔥🤣
My NEW HIIT Cardio & Abs program has just launched in the Sweat app, and I cannot wait for you all to try it!!

If you are looking for a challenge, these workouts have been designed with you in mind! It's fast, it's quick, but it's definitely not easy! This program is perfect for completing at home with minimal equipment, but you can absolutely complete this in the gym too. These exercises focus on strengthening your core, so get ready to feel the burn! 

Here are my 5 FAVOURITE AB exercises from my new program, that will definitely give your core a workout:

💥 Flutters
💥 Russian Twist
💥 Alternating Jackknife
💥 Side Plank & Oblique Crunch
💥 X Mountain Climbers

I think my abs are actually on fire after these exercises 🤣

#SWKCommunity, have you tried my new program yet? What are your favourite exercises from HIIT Cardio & Abs? Let me know below! 

#SweatMade #SweatwithKayla #SWK #SweatCommunity #Workout #SWKCommunity #fitness 

www.kaylaitsines.com/CardioAndAbs

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by KAYLA ITSINES on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Being fit, healthy, it's only part of the story. Training isn't just about building a strong body, it's about giving you self self-worth a workout.'.

node.text:
Strength comes in so many forms, both physically and mentally. Lifted that new PB you didn’t think you could do? Finally mastered your pushups? Got that full chin-up you have been trying to do for months? Got your first full burpee? INCREDIBLE!! 

However, the physical changes that have happened might be why you started, but it's definitely not all you've gained. Training builds your strength, but it also brings out your determination, perseverance, your confidence in your abilities, and your power. It's getting that big rush of endorphins at the end of your workout, the feeling of pride when you know you've smashed a goal, your determination when you think you just can't get one more rep in. 

I want you to feel PROUD when you achieve these things, no matter how big or how small your goal is.

YOU worked hard to get to this point. YOU kept going when it wasn't always easy. 

YOU did this ❤️

#SweatMade #SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #Motivation #Quote #Fitness

www.kaylaitsines.com/CardioAndAbs

node.text:
As a personal trainer, I am lucky enough to see women work towards their goals every single day. 

I love that I can be a small part of someone's journey. To encourage, to support and to motivate my clients and community in search of a better, stronger you.

Over the years, I've seen sweat, smiles, tears, and moments of disbelief when new potential is unlocked. 

I've celebrated with you. 

Cried with you. 

And pushed through painful workouts with you.

Whether you train with me in person, or in the @Sweat app... I am always here to cheer you on, but remember, it is YOU that is doing the work.

YOU are the one showing up for your workout.

YOU are the one pushing past the excuses.

YOU are the one that is achieving the 'impossible' and unlocking new potential.

Honestly, YOU are the reason @Sweat exists. And YOU are the core of what #SweatMade is all about. 

As your personal trainer, I want to help as many of you ladies as possible on this journey.

Because the best version of you, she's waiting to sweat.

I am #SweatMade. Are you?

#SweatMade #SWK #SweatCommunity #SweatApp #SWKCommunity #SweatWithKayla #workout #fitness #health 

www.kaylaitsines.com/CardioandAbs

SO if you haven’t heard already, I just launched my new HIIT Cardio & Abs program in the @Sweat App 😍
.... and here’s 5 reasons why I LOVE it ☝️❤️

So if you’re watching this and thinking.... YEP, I WANT TO DO THIS I LOVE HIIT.... Then you’re probably right as I have designed this program for all the people out there that LOVE HIIT just as much as I do! 😍

And for those that are curious to try it but are too intimidated, I want you to remember that everyone starts somewhere. HIIT isn’t easy, but you can learn to love it just as so many women in the #SWKCommunity have.

All you need to do is try, and you can do that for FREE right now!

Just download @Sweat’s using our 7-day free trial & get ready for a fast-paced & fun workout with me, as your trainer. 💪

Link in bio!
I’ll see you there 😊

http://www.kaylaitsines.com/CardioandAbs

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #SweatApp #Workout #HIIT #fitness

🔥🔥 CALLING ALL HIIT LOVERS 🔥🔥
We have just dropped 4 NEW HIIT PROGRAMS in the Sweat app just for YOU! 😍

I am so happy that I can finally share that today, we have released FOUR new High intensity programs in the @Sweat app… including a brand new HIIT program of my own which I am SO excited about! 

All of these programs can all be completed in about 20-30 minutes and they are designed to be intense, fast and fun… which is exactly how I love to train, so I hope you’ll love them, too! 

The new programs are:
🔥HIIT CARDIO & ABS WITH... ME! 👋

🔥HIGH INTENSITY BARRE WITH BRITANY 
- @britanywilliams 

🔥FULL BODY HIIT WITH CHONTEL
- @chontelduncan 

🔥HIIT WITH MONICA ..... who ladies, is also the newest trainer to the Sweat family! Welcome @trainwithmon! 🎉

Watch this video to find out exactly which HIIT program is best for you, while I demonstrate a few of my favorite exercises from each program. 👆

LADIES... if you LOVE the feeling after a HIIT workout or want to try it for the first time... all you need is the @Sweat app.

You can try any of these new HIIT programs for FREE today by downloading @Sweat using our 7 Day free trial (link in bio)!

I CAN'T WAIT FOR YOU TO TRY THESE, #SWKCOMMUNITY! ❤️😍

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #Sweat #HIIT #Workout #Fitness #SweatMade
